# Keep secrets, local data, and bulky/irrelevant files out of ANY Docker build context.
#
# This is a safety net for the bridge image (see bridge/Dockerfile), whose context is the
# repo root. Most importantly it guarantees a real `.env` or an exported snapshot/database
# can never be copied into an image, even if one is present in the working tree.

# Secrets — never copy a real .env into an image (the placeholder .env.example is harmless
# but also unneeded at runtime, so it stays out too).
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Dependencies / build output / VCS / CI — not needed in the build-free bridge image.
**/node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
.git
.github
coverage
.vite
*.tsbuildinfo

# Real inventory data must never enter an image (config points at a mounted snapshot).
bridge/local/
**/*.sqlite
**/*.db
**/gubbins-sync.json
